description:
Han Sheng Tang

A well-known Chinese medicine pharmaceutical company is looking for suitable candidates to join our team.

Production Manager

Job Highlights

Work closely with QA, QC and Engineering departments
HKGMP standard
5 yrs. exp. Chinese medicine pharmaceutical industry

Job Description

Responsibilities:

Prepare and review protocols and other associated HKGMP documentation;
Plan, organize and lead the production department to achieve company’s business objectives;
Act as a key person of a HKGMP standard pharmaceutical plant;
Ensure compliance to health, safety and regulatory requirements of all products manufactured;
Work closely with QA, QC and Engineering departments to achieve company’s goals on HKGMP;
Monitor the equipment, cleanroom and warehouse according to the approved GMP procedures;
Involve in design of various manufacturing process flows in the pharmaceutical plant;
Manage GMP documents e.g. batch production records, manufacturing instructions, SOPs, etc.;
Involve in design and monitoring of Qualification, Process Validation & Cleaning Validation processes;
Oversee production activities, including control of production process and production facilities;
Perform ad-hoc duties as assigned.

Requirements:

Bachelor or above in Science or Engineering related disciplines e.g. Pharmaceutical Technology, Chinese Medicine, Total Quality Management, etc.;
5 years’ experience in GMP Chinese Medicine Pharmaceutical manufacturing field in supervisory or managerial level;
Applicant with experience of HKGMP application would be a great advantage;
Applicant with knowledge of industrial engineering / mechanical engineering would be an advantage;
Good organization, communication, management and training skills;
Be accountable and able to solve practical problems in manufacturing;
Independent, enthusiastic and a good team player;
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Production Manager;
 Immediate availability is preferred.

Interested parties please send full resume with date available and expected salary for interview.

(All personal data collected will be kept in the strictest confidence and to be used for recruitment purpose only.)

Job Duties:

Participate in manufacturing & quality control of In-vitro diagnosis reagents;
Monitor and review of manufacturing and quality control process;
Coordinate with multi-functional teams for new product launching;
Perform materials sourcing and quality control of incoming materials;
Review and update standard operation procedure and documents;
Provide technical training to ensure strictly follows to the approved SOP;
Assist in QMS accreditation and product registration;
Plan and perform stability study of new products;
Monitor and maintenance production facility and equipment.

Requirements:

Postgraduate, degree or diploma holder in life science or related discipline with knowledge in molecular genetics / molecular biology;
1 year of manufacturing experience in pharmaceutical, medical device or health care products;
Experienced in PCR or molecular lab is preferred;
Experience in handling equipment maintenance and calibration work;
Knowledge in ISO 9001, ISO 13485 or GMP / six sigma is an advantage;
Good written and verbal communication skills;
Good problem solving skill and able to work under pressure;
Team player attitude, proactive and self-motivated.

If you are passionate, driven and looking for a new and exciting opportunity within a successful and growing company, this may be the right role for you.

Please click “Apply Now” to submit your application.

For more info, please visit our web page at http://www.diagcorlifescience.com/

We will only consider applicants who apply directly to our firm and not through recruitment agencies. All applications will be treated in strict confidence. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 4 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and the applications will be destroyed within 6

About E Fund Management (Hong Kong) Co., Limited
E Fund Management (HK) Co., Ltd (“E Fund HK”) was officially established in 2008 and is licensed by the Securities and Futures Commission of Hong Kong to conduct Type 1 (Dealing in Securities), Type 4 (Advising on Securities) and Type 9 (Asset Management) regulated activities*. As the international business platform of E Fund, E Fund HK provides bilateral and cross-border asset management services in equity, fixed income and global asset allocation for investors all over the world. E Fund HK has an established presence in Hong Kong for many years and has since listed a number of mutual funds, private equity funds and ETFs in Hong Kong, Europe and the US. Its award-winning products have been recognized by leading institutions such as Morningstar, Lipper, AsianInvestor and Benchmark for their strong performances relative to peers.
E Fund, the parent company of E Fund HK, was founded in 2001 and headquartered in Guangzhou. It has branch offices in Beijing, Guangzhou, Shanghai, and subsidiaries including E Fund International Holdings Limited (with E Fund Management (HK) Co., Limited under it), and E Fund Asset Management Co., Ltd.E Fund has grown tremendously to become the largest integrated management corporations in China with total assets under management about RMB 1.8 trillion (USD 268 billion) as of September 30, 2020 (including E Fund HK and China subsidiaries)**. E Fund is one of the few companies within the China fund management industry who is in possession of all business licenses for the provision of asset management services including China mutual funds, social security funds, pension insurance funds, corporate pension funds, segregated accounts, QDII, and for global investors: QFII, RQFII. E Fund passed the independent verification of the Global Investment Performance Standards (GIPS) in August 2014, signifying an important step forward to become more internationalized with unified performance reporting.
Leveraging the investment and research ability of E Fund, E Fund HK establishes an integrated investment research platform, which has covered three major segments, namely fixed income, equity and global asset allocation. E Fund HK also has an efficient operation team that can meet the various needs of the products registered in Mainland China, Hong Kong, Cayman Islands, Europe (UCITS), United States, and other countries and regions. Integrated with E Fund’s global expansion strategies, E Fund HK is committed to providing professional asset management services for global investors and let them share the fruits of Chinese economic growth. Via the construction of a global asset allocation platform, E Fund HK serves as a window to help investors in China to achieve exposures all over the world.

Responsibilities
• Develop, build and sustain professional relationships with institutional clients and utilize these relationships to promote business;
• Formulate business strategies and plans for growing the institutional sales business with emphasis on business AUM development and market penetration to Hong Kong and Mainland China market;
• Achieve and exceed revenue targets;
• Drive and lead internal and external coordination to meet and provide products necessary to meet client’s requirements;
• Provide total financial asset management solutions to institutional clients;
• Management of marketing roadmap and Client events.

Requirements
• Advanced degree in economics, finance or related disciplines from leading universities;
• Familiar with related field, 6-10 years’ related experience is advantage;
• Relevant experience in Mainland China strongly preferred;
• Familiar with Mainland China market;
• Fluent in spoken and written in English and Mandarin;
• Efficient, proactive and responsible;
• Strong team player with excellent inter-personal skills;
• Organize and ability to prioritize; multi-task & work well under tight deadlines and pressure, reliable and detail mined;
• Senior candidates may be considered as Product Director.

Compensation and Benefits
E Fund HK is a fast growing company with strong financial resources and parent company support. We offer competitive compensations and career growth opportunities. We also offer attractive benefit programs and continued education support.

Key Roles and Responsibilities:

Assist in developing, implementing and maintaining the documentation system and quality management system;
Perform routine inspection on products at various stages on the production line to implement the GMP policy;
Assist in performing ad hoc project and other QA-related duties.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or Degree holder in Pharmaceutical Studies or other science related discipline;
Hands-on GMP experience in pharmaceutical industry will be an definite advantage;
Hardworking, initiative, self-motivated and fast learner;
Strong communication skill, good command of English and Chinese;
Good knowledge of MS Office and Chinese word processing;
Fresh graduates are also considered.



We offer to the right candidates with competitive remuneration package including 12-16 day annual leave, marriage leave, maternity leave, paternity leave, compassionate leave, Public Holidays, medical and dental insurance, educational sponsorship, overtime allowance, performance bonus, MPF and other fringe benefits.

How to Apply

You are invited to send in your application and CV stating the position you are applying for together with your current and expected salary by clicking the "apply button".

 
